        <article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_41478389" data-cid="41478389">
    <div id="comment_41478389">
        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Refund how?"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Refund how?<span> (4, Interesting)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~nedlohs" class="author" title="author name and user ID">nedlohs (1335013) </a> | about 2 years ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3148631&cid=41478389">(#41478389)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_41478389" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>If they didn't contract to refund in such cases then they aren't insolvent since there is no obligation to repay. If they did then if the terms for repaying are long enough in the contract they probably aren't insolvent either (you are allowed to carry debt without that automatically making you insolvent). If they do have such a contract but the penalties for breaking it are small enough or allowed to be paid over a long enough term then the same thing applies as above - you are allowed to have debt.</p><p>So what information leads you to conclude they are insolvent?</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_41478389">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3148631" data-cid="41478389">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="41478389" data-pid="41478389" data-cid="41478389"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
