<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_41480185" data-cid="41480185">
    <div id="comment_41480185">
        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:pump and dump"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:pump and dump<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~IamTheRealMike" class="author" title="author name and user ID">IamTheRealMike (537420) </a> | about 2 years ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3148631&cid=41480185">(#41480185)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_41480185" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">That's incorrect. The codebase uses the term "coin" to refer to a transaction output, ie a discrete unit of value that can be claimed by the holder of a private key. There can be multiple outputs/coins sent to the same address. Internally Bitcoin has almost no notion of balance - the balance you see in your wallet app is merely the sum of unspent outputs.</div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_41480185">
